@startuml
' Rendered to fanout.svg by .github/workflows/plantuml.yml (docs/ABC.puml →
' docs/ABC.svg). Keep @startuml bare: a named @startuml would override the
' output filename and break that convention. To preview locally, run
' `make diagrams` (same pinned renderer as CI; see PLANTUML_IMAGE in the
' Makefile).
'
' Source of truth: internal/grain/room/fanout.go (jobs, dispatcher, worker)
' and room.go (spawn site, command handlers). ADR-015 carries the design.

participant "Sender's\nUser grain" as sender
participant "Room grain" as room
participant "Fan-out child\n(long-lived worker)" as worker
participant "Each member's\nUser grain" as member
database "PostgreSQL" as db

sender -> room : PostMessage
room -> room : validate membership
room -> db : persist the message
room -> room : snapshot recipients,\nbuild immutable payload
room -> worker : Send(fanout job)\n(fire and forget)
room --> sender : PostMessageResponse

note over sender, worker
  The grain's mailbox is free the moment the job is queued.
  The sender's own echo below therefore cannot deadlock:
  it targets a User grain that is no longer blocked on the
  Room grain's reply. (ADR-015)
end note

loop for every member, the sender included
  worker -> member : ForwardMessage
  member -> member : deliver to each\nregistered connection
end
note right of worker
  Best effort: a failed recipient is
  logged (grain.fanout.error) and
  skipped, never aborting the rest.
end note
@enduml
